
# Line Segment Information GUI

## Author
Jeremiah E. Ochepo

## Last Edited
3/1/2020 (10PM)

## Description
This program creates a simple graphical user interface (GUI) to visualize and retrieve information about a line segment.

## Features
- Draws a fixed line on the GUI.
- Allows the user to define a line segment by clicking two points.
- Displays the slope and length of the drawn line segment.

## Requirements
- Python 3.x
- [graphics library](https://pypi.org/project/graphics.py/)

## Usage
1. Run the program.
2. Click two points on the GUI to define a line segment.
3. The program will display the slope and length of the line segment.
4. Close the GUI by clicking anywhere.

## Notes
- The program uses the `graphics` library, make sure it is installed (`pip install graphics.py`).

## Troubleshooting
- If you encounter any issues, feel free to contact the author.

